            <div class="details-sub-header">Chapel at University College, Oxford </div>




    <p>We are looking forward to getting married on <b> Saturday 17th July 2021</b> in Oxford, the city where we first met 8 years ago. The ceremony will be held in the Chapel of University College, Oxford, which is where Genny was a student.
    </p>
    <p>
    University College is situated in the centre of the City on the <a href="https://www.google.co.uk/maps/place/University+College/@51.7525769,-1.2542868,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x4876c6ae75e1910f:0xe200d6141ce01e30!8m2!3d51.7525769!4d-1.2520981" target="_blank"> High Street, OX1 4BH</a>. The main entrance to the college is a big brown door, which is up a few steps. There are two big brown doors â€“ the entrance is the one furthest to the right as you look at college, opposite a red phone box.  
    </p>
    <p>
    Please note there is no parking at the college and parking in Oxford is extremely limited. If you are coming by car then we recommend that you leave your car at the <a href="https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/roads-and-transport/public-transport/park-and-ride" target="_blank"> Park and Ride </a> - there are more details on the <%= link_to 'Travel', controller: 'travel' %> page.
    </p>
    <p>
    If you walk straight down the path in front of you as you enter the college, the chapel is at the other end of the quad through a door to the left of a passageway. The ceremony starts at 2pm so please arrive from 1.30pm to make sure you are seated in time. The ceremony will last for approximately 30 minutes.
    </p>


